<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
The {foo} in your pack appears to be cursed (or was it average?). Anyhow I was wearing it, it wasn't in the pack... <hr>
 <p>
Tries to wear a drum, while already wearing another drum {cursed}: "the drum you are shooting with appears to be cursed"...   well I'm not *shooting* with a drum anytime soon! 
</p>
<p>
I vaguely recall something silly about the tool slot, but I can't remember if it was the notify. Maybe it was just the vampiric/earthquake-causing digger that caused my weapons to make earthquakes?? 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: An error similar to those above: While wearing a cursed climbing set and trying to wear another tool: "the climbing set you are carrying in your pack seems to be cursed". 
</p>
<p>
These bugs seem to be related to an outdated describe_use() function. There are missing slots and instruments need another message: 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 instrument: The drum you are "playing" appears to be cursed. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 ammo: The arrows you are "carring in your quiver" ... 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 tool: The shovel / climbing set you are "using as a tool" ... 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: Fixed in ToME 2.3.0. Perhaps there are some other issues, but this fix should solve the reported problems. 
</p>
